      "body" : "> @practicalswift yes, announcing bugs with exploit guidelines 30 days after a fix is released would put a ton of our users at massive risk.\r\n\r\nSure. However it's still a hell of a lot better than being willfully ignorant of vulnerabilities, that could be independently found anyway. But yeah, it'd be great if they extended that deadline for bitcoin but if not, I don't see the big deal. And the damages of public disclosure can be heavily mitigated by a few days prior widely publizing the need to update.",
